cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use these findings, figures, or code, please cite this repository."
title: "nanogpt-experiments: small, verifiable experiments on how tiny transformers learn"
abstract: >-
  A growing meta-repo of small, self-contained, fully-instrumented experiments on a
  tiny nanoGPT, aimed at understanding how LLMs actually learn — training dynamics,
  optimizers, generalization, and the developmental emergence and universality of
  internal (world-model) representations, studied with controlled ground-truth probes.
type: software
